Gene Kelly was born on August 23, 1912 (age 83) in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, United States. He is a Celebrity Singer, Dancer, Actor, Film director, Choreographer, Film Producer, Television producer. Popular actor and dancer who choreographed his own dance routines in such hit 1940s and '50s films as Singin' in the Rain (movie), Anchors Aweigh, An American in Paris and On the Town. He was ranked 15th on the American Film Institute's list of the Greatest Male Stars of All Time in 1999. According to numerology, Gene Kelly's Life Path Number is 8. His the best movies are Singin' in the Rain (1952), An American in Paris (1951), The Young Girls of Rochefort (1967), On the Town (1949) and Brigadoon (1954). His education: Peabody High School.
